The paper deals with network protection strategies in optical networks, which involves aspects of network infrastructure (NI), information theory (IT), and robotics (RO) in terms of deploying the proposed strategies. The paper also discusses capacity reduction, which is a topic in distributed computing (DC), and the use of network coding, which is a topic in social and information networks (SI).
